To find out when the ball will hit the ground, we set $y$, the height, to zero and solve for $t$:
\begin{align*}
-6t^2 - 10t + 56 &= 0 \\
\Rightarrow \quad 6t^2 + 10t - 56 &= 0 \\
\end{align*}
We then divide the equation by 2 to simplify it:
\begin{align*}
\Rightarrow \quad 3t^2 + 5t - 28 &= 0 \\
\end{align*}
Next, we factor the quadratic equation:
\begin{align*}
\Rightarrow \quad (3t-7)(t+4) &= 0.
\end{align*}
We then set each factor equal to zero and solve for $t$:
\begin{align*}
3t - 7 = 0 \quad &\text{or} \quad t + 4 = 0 \\
t = \frac{7}{3} \quad &\text{or} \quad t = -4
\end{align*}
Since time cannot be negative, we choose the positive value for $t$:
\begin{align*}
t = \frac{7}{3}
\end{align*}
Converting the fraction to a decimal to express the time in seconds rounded to the nearest hundredth:
\begin{align*}
t \approx 2.33
\end{align*}
Final Answer: 2.33

